msgid "the :option:`cmake --install-prefix` option;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guide/tutorial/Installation Commands and Concepts.rst:76
msgid ""
"the :ref:`installDir <CMakePresets.configurePresets.installDir>` field in "
"CMake presets; or"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guide/tutorial/Installation Commands and Concepts.rst:78
msgid "the :variable:`CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX` variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guide/tutorial/Installation Commands and Concepts.rst:81
msgid ""
"We have discouraged setting ``CMAKE_`` variables inside the project. "
"Setting :variable:`CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX` is *particularly* bad practice "
"without very good reasoning for doing so, since it prevents users from ever "
"overriding it. When providing a default, projects should check :variable:"
"`CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX_INITIALIZED_TO_DEFAULT`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guide/tutorial/Installation Commands and Concepts.rst:87
msgid ""
"Alternatively, we can use the :option:`cmake --install --prefix <cmake--"
